METASPLOIT - Metasploit is a penetration testing framework used to find, test, and exploit security vulnerabilities in systems.



search - searches for exploits
info - Shows details about a module
back - Go back from a module

use - selects exploit 
show targets - Shows supported target systems for the exploit
show options - shows options for the exploit
show payloads - Shows available payloads for the selected exploit

exploit/run - runs the exploit to take advantage of the vulnerability and attempt to gain access to the target system
set payload - selects the code that will run if the exploit succeeds and before/when access is gained

set SESSION - selects the session
sessions - lists sessions
-k - kills session
-u tries to upgrade session
-i use session


setg - set as a global varible 
unset - unsets the varible 

set LHOST — Your local IP address 
set LPORT — Your listening port
set RHOST — Target IP address
set RPORT — Target port

